letter:
From: Philip Kirkbride

The content and settings of this e-card can be modified for re-use by non-programmers. The data is contained in 'data/ecard.json'. The use of json rather than a database was chosen in order to make this card portable and self contained.

Changes can be made by modifying the json. The data folder also contains a json scema file which can be used with a json-schema based builder to allow building of json with a GUI.

The example json includes 3 ways to use the image src attribute base64, local, and web hosted. The third method web-hosted is significantly slower and you will likely see a lag on the second click of the above image. For maximum speed I recommend using base64.
